                     <interp inst="t18230910-218-defend1996" type="age" value="23"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18230910-218-off1188" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18230910-218-off1188" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-218-off1188" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18230910-218-cd1189" type="crimeDate">22d of July</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-218-off1188 t18230910-218-cd1189"></join>, a pillow, value 2 s.; a pillow-case, value 6 d.; five knives, value 1 s.; six forks, value 1 s.; a blanket, value 6 d.; two pair of stockings, value 1 s., and two half-handkerchiefs, value 1 s.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               
                  <persName id="t18230910-218-victim1998" type="victimName">
                     John 
                     Gifford
                  <interp inst="t18230910-218-victim1998" type="surname" value="Gifford"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-218-victim1998" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-218-victim1998" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-218-off1188 t18230910-218-victim1998"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            , her master.</p>
               <p>MR. ADOLPHUS conducted the prosecution.</p>
               <p>MR. 
               <persName id="t18230910-218-person1999">
                  JOHN 
                  GIFFORD
               <interp inst="t18230910-218-person1999" type="surname" value="GIFFORD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-218-person1999" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-218-person1999" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live on <placeName id="t18230910-218-crimeloc1190">Muswellhill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-218-crimeloc1190" type="placeName" value="Muswellhill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-218-crimeloc1190" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-218-off1188 t18230910-218-crimeloc1190"></join>. The prisoner was in my service, as <rs id="t18230910-218-deflabel1191" type="occupation">cook</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-218-defend1996 t18230910-218-deflabel1191"></join>, up to the 22d of July - she had been with us more than a year - after she was gone we missed the articles stated in the indictment; among others, I found she lodged with one Glascott, in the neighbourhood - I went there with an officer, and found her at home in a room up one pair of stairs - she said she knew nothing about it; search was made in her presence; a pillow and case found on her bed, and inside the pillow, among the feathers, were five knives and six forks - they were parlour knives, and had never been used - we missed more - the initials were nearly picked out of the pillowcase; but the thread holes were visible. I found a blanket and two pair of stockings, with the marks on; I believe I had never worn them; I never gave her any stockings; they were tied up in a pair of stockings belonging to a man who had formerly lived with me. A cravat of mine had been cut in two; I found half of it on her neck with my name on it at full length.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by Mr. ALLEY. Q. You took her with a good character from a friend of your's - A. No, she came from Wales; she broke her collar-bone some time ago.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-218-person2000">
                  ELIZA 
                  GLASSCOTT
               <interp inst="t18230910-218-person2000" type="surname" value="GLASSCOTT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-218-person2000" type="given" value="ELIZA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-218-person2000" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live on Muswell-hill; the prisoner lodged on my first floor in July or August; and lodged there when the prosecutor came - she lodged there alone.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-218-person2001">
                  JOHN 
                  CONWAY
               <interp inst="t18230910-218-person2001" type="surname" value="CONWAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-218-person2001" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-218-person2001" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I assisted in the search, and found the property.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. About four months before I left her service, I wanted a flannel for a house-cloth; she told me to take the ironing blanket - I kept the blanket, and cut up some old petticoats of my own. I broke my collar-bone, and had a pillow of my own, and took the wrong one away. The prosecutor said before I left, that he would do me all the injury he could on account of my leaving his service to be married.</p>
               <p>MR. GIFFORD. I never used any such language.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-218-person2002">
                  ANN 
                  HORTON
               <interp inst="t18230910-218-person2002" type="surname" value="HORTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-218-person2002" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-218-person2002" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mr. Gifford. I never knew that the prisoner had a pillow of her own.</p>
